    <exercise>
      <p>
        Previously we computed <m>\int \tan(\theta)\dx{\theta}</m> using the
        identity <m>\tan(\theta)=\frac{\cos(\theta)}{\sin(\theta)}</m>. We
        could also use the identity
        <m>\tan(\theta)=\frac{\sec(\theta)\tan(\theta)}{\sec(\theta)}\dx{\theta}</m>.
