    </exercise>
    <p>
      The same tricks we applied with secant and tangent would apply equally
      well to integrals involving cosecant and cotangent using the
      identity <m>\csc^2(\theta)=1+\cot^2(\theta)</m>. Of course, we have not covered every
      type of integral that can occur and you can always find integrals that
      will take other tricks. We’ve only provided some basics that you can
      build on as you gain experience. So practice, practice, practice!
    </p>
