  <p>
    With all of this set up, what we really want is the horizontal component of the force <m>T</m> to be <m>h</m> and the vertical component to be the weight of the bridge from <m>0</m> to <m>x</m>, namely, <m>wA</m>.  This leads to the following picture.
  </p>
    <figure>
<caption>
Stone Arch Triangle of Forces
