  <p>
    This leads to the slope of the tangent line at <m>P</m> equaling <m>\frac{wA}{h}</m>, so we get the differential equation
    <me>\dfdx{y}{x}=\frac{w}{h}A.</me>
    The problem here is that we don’t know what <m>A</m> is.  However, a moment’s thought tells us that we know what <m>\dx{A}{}</m> is.  If we increase <m>x</m> to <m>x+\dx{x}{}</m>, then we can see that <m>\dx{A}=y\dx{x}{}</m>.
  </p>
